main event: On June 3, 1955, a sighting of a red to green object with a tail like a shooting star was reported at Paine AFB, Washington. The object changed to a high altitude bright object before being observed as two 1-1/2 types side by side, shining.
interesting points: The object was initially observed as a round, red to green object with a tail like a shooting star, which then changed to a high altitude bright object.
Two 1-1/2 types were observed side by side, shining in the same direction.
There were two B-47's tracking in the same area at the time of the sighting.
AACS squadron was tracking two military aircraft in the area, but neither the aircraft nor the observer saw the two shining objects.
The length of observation of the objects was reported to be 1-2 (5) minutes.
sighted object: red to green object with a tail like a shooting star, later observed as two 1-1/2 types side by side, shining
